A vintage 1970s technical illustration style image depicting an intricate brass and copper clockwork mechanism where multiple gears of different sizes interlock precisely, with some gears appearing as filing cabinet drawers slightly open revealing paper documents inside, while other gears contain tiny grid patterns resembling database tables. The mechanism sits on a mahogany desk surface with warm amber lighting casting long shadows, thin copper pipes connecting various components like data flowing between systems, small glass windows in the housing revealing the inner workings, rendered with crosshatching and aged paper texture typical of old engineering manuals.
